The paper proposes a method for learning interpretable representations for regression using neural networks and other elementary functions. This falls under the category of machine learning, specifically in the subfield of representation learning. The paper also discusses optimization techniques and benchmarks the proposed method against state-of-the-art machine learning approaches. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
